---
title: Pan Seared Sea Bass with New Potatoes and Cucumber-Dill Relish
description: The star of this delicious summery dish is the sea bass from the guys over at J.K. Mayfair (who also supply fish to the Queen!). The trick with getting a crispy skin on your fish is to use a medium-hot pan, and while the skin is cooking, try not to move the fish…it’s that easy!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/57223771f8b25ea3388b4569.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/57223771f8b25ea3388b4569.pdf
cuisine: Fusion
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 359 kcal
  fat: 9 g
  saturated fat: 2 g
  carbohydrates: 38 g
  protein: 33 g
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/pan-seared-sea-bass-with-new-potatoes-20-57223771f8b25ea3388b4569
---

Peel the outside green part of the @cucumber{1/2} and discard. Peel strips of cucumber
lengthways all the way round (you won't need the squidgy seeds in the middle). Peel and
very thinly slice half the @red onion{1/4}(thinly sliced) into half moon shapes (you want
this as thin as your knife skills allow).

Mix the cucumber and onion slices with @salt{1/4%tbsp} and leave in a #colander{} for
~{10%mins}.

> If you don't like raw onion, leave it out at this stage and add it in at the end.

Put a large #pot{} of water on to boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Wash the @new potatoes{1}
and cut into quarters. Cook in the boiling water for ~{10-15%mins} or until just tender.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Squeeze the moisture out of the cucumber and onion (preferably between a few sheets of
#kitchen paper{}). Then rinse under cold running water. Mix the @white wine vinegar{1}
in a #bowl{} with @sugar{1/2%tsp} (if you have some) until dissolved. Add three-quarters
of your dressing (keep the rest for later) to your cucumber and onion mixture. Put in
your fridge until needed.

Heat a large #frying pan{} with @oil{1%tbsp} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the
@sea bass fillets{2} skin-side down and season the flesh-side with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}. Cook for ~{3-4%mins} then turn over and turn off the heat,
letting the residual heat from the pan cook the other side.

Finely chop the @dill{2} and mix through your cucumber relish at the last moment. Taste
for seasoning and add more salt or pepper as needed.

Make the salad by picking the leaves from the @baby gem lettuce{1} and adding a drizzle
of @olive oil{}, a small pinch of salt and pepper and the remaining dressing. Toss your
potatoes in a drizzle of olive oil and another pinch of salt and pepper if needed. Serve
the new potatoes topped with your seared sea bass, a generous helping of your cucumber
relish and the baby gem lettuce.